annotation.TEXT: I wanted to be sure not to puncture my head on this thing.

Nope, didn't land on that spike at the end. Yay! Oh, geez... I remember this part giving me some trouble on Easy Mode.

And now to go up, where I should find...

Meow, ray hit barn!
Alright, so now the Purple Zone is officially complete! So, let's see what people voted for over the last couple episodes...

Nice. That trinket was no problem to get.

SNAAAIIILLL!!!

Yes! I'm glad moving straight to the left on that last part worked! Oh, man... This room again, and it's clearly way harder.
So, Red Zone it is! But, first... I want to get another trinket from the hub area.
(Is that the name of an Australian airline or something?)

1 vote for 333333-1, 2 votes for VVVVVV with danmaku, 1 vote to SAY NO TO RACISM, 1 vote for me to actually be good at this game, 1 vote for Super Pika Land Ultra, The Second Reality Project Reloaded, and Mushroom Kingdom Meltdown, 2 votes for Blue Zone, and 7 votes for Red Zone!

Red Zone start! I wonder how painful an experience this'll be for me and Viridian...

...a dudette!

And that would be the trinket I was going for here! Hmm... I'm not sure if there are any left in the hub area, but if I don't have twenty after finishing the Red and Blue Zones, then that'll clue me in.
Ow, need 5 more red coins for the power star!
Ow, my pants zipper!
Looks like it's a bit harder to get to the other side.
Oh, come on. I'm sure I was only barely tapping right there.
So, next time, hopefully I'll finish up the Red Zone and maybe get started on the Blue Zone if things go well. To be continued...
Wombat Henry Air!

The lower part of this room is definitely way trickier than on Easy Mode, that's for sure.

And, surprisingly, I got out of there painlessly. Now, I'm not going to the Blue Zone next. Instead, I'm headed to the Red Zone, which is conveniently right over here.
I actually want to take the lower route here this time, since I believe it'll lead to the trinket I'm thinking of.
Yes, finally!
Ow, I need 7 more red coins to get a power star!
Alright, good. Next up is that trinket, but I want to see if there's a checkpoint right up here first... And there is, which is great.

Dang it! This better not be the whole rest of the video right here!

Inb4 I land on this spike.

And it looks like I'm going to get through it no problem here on Hard Mode as well.

Freaking heck, Google and your malfunctioning annotation save function after I've had the editor open for a few hours. It broke sometime as I was placing the "Ow, my kicking and screaming legs!" annotation at 10:46 this time, and I had to redo five annotations as a result!
And now let's get started here... I've gotta go in between these snowflake-shurikens with the right timing...

Also, TRINKEEETTT!!!
